# SPA fallback: every unmatched path (e.g. /TFRC/) is a client-rendered gene
# page — serve the shell and let its JS read the symbol from window.location.
#
# Target the canonical `/gene/`, NOT `/gene/index.html`: with
# `trailingSlash: true` Cloudflare Pages 308-redirects the `index.html` form to
# `/gene/`, and that canonicalization breaks `/gene/index.html` as a 200-rewrite
# target (the rule silently falls through to 404.html — the bug this fixes).
# `/gene/` serves the shell asset with a clean 200.
#
# Real static routes (/, /benchmark/, /_next/*, /data/*, sitemap.xml) match an
# asset first — static assets take precedence over _redirects — so this splat
# only ever fires for the per-gene URLs.
/*  /gene/  200
